AMEND S e n ate Bill No. 1083 House Bill No. 622*
by adding the following as a preamble before the enacting clause:
WHEREAS, diversity, equity, inclusion (DEI) has been weaponized in this country; and
WHEREAS, since 2023 at least 256 bills have been introduced in states attacking DEI in
different governmental settings and at least twenty states have at least one law that bans DEI
practices in government; and
WHEREAS, since 2023 at least 157 bills explicitly attacking DEI in education have been
introduced in thirty-four states and fifteen states have passed the bans or restrictions into law;
and
WHEREAS, since 2023, 226 bills explicitly attacking DEI in private business have been
introduced across thirty-six states with sixteen states enacting such laws; and
WHEREAS, the Social Security Administration, in the 2021-2022 period, reported that
the median annual earnings of White, non-Hispanic men in the 20-29 age group were 34%
higher than Black, non-Hispanic men; and
WHEREAS, the Social Security Administration, in the 2021-2022 period, reported that
the median annual earnings of White, non-Hispanic men in the 50-59 age group were 49%
higher than Black, non-Hispanic men; now, therefore,
AND FURTHER AMEND by deleting SECTION 1 and substituting instead:
SECTION 1. This act is known and may be cited as the "Caucasian Male Prosperity
Act."
